746
01:12:20,960 --> 01:12:22,916
I think we should call the hospital.

747
01:12:26,040 --> 01:12:26,995
OK.

748
01:12:30,640 --> 01:12:31,595
Go on.

749
01:12:31,800 --> 01:12:33,119
[dial tone]

750
01:12:33,320 --> 01:12:35,515
Go on.

751
01:12:35,720 --> 01:12:37,676
Is that what you wanna do?

752
01:12:39,000 --> 01:12:40,956
Call them.

753
01:13:05,320 --> 01:13:07,276
I'm not a murderer.

754
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:10,756
I'm not...

755
01:13:11,400 --> 01:13:15,075
Trevor, you were all I had left.

756
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:25,355
[bleeping]

757
01:13:36,320 --> 01:13:38,276
It's over.

758
01:13:49,400 --> 01:13:52,836
[recording] <i>If you'd like to make</i>
<i>a call, hang up and try again.</i>

759
01:14:13,000 --> 01:14:15,230
[Candyman] <i>They will all abandon you.</i>

760
01:14:26,560 --> 01:14:30,758
<i>All you have left</i>
<i>is my desire for you.</i>

761
01:14:50,320 --> 01:14:53,278
[laughing, chattering]

762
01:16:47,360 --> 01:16:50,477
[shouting]

763
01:17:14,600 --> 01:17:16,556
[breathing]

764
01:17:51,760 --> 01:17:53,716
[steady breathing]

765
01:18:10,720 --> 01:18:12,278
Helen...

766
01:18:14,640 --> 01:18:16,596
You came to me.

767
01:18:18,800 --> 01:18:20,756
The child...

768
01:18:23,240 --> 01:18:27,711
- We had a deal.
- Surrender to me now...

769
01:18:27,920 --> 01:18:30,434
...and he shall be unharmed.

770
01:18:41,840 --> 01:18:44,832
- We have a bargain.
- But I'm afraid.

771
01:18:45,040 --> 01:18:47,998
Do you fear the pain,
or what is beyond?

772
01:18:48,200 --> 01:18:49,155
Both.

773
01:18:49,360 --> 01:18:53,399
The pain, I can assure you,
will be exquisite.

774
01:18:53,600 --> 01:18:56,512
As for our deaths,
there is nothing to fear.

775
01:18:58,040 --> 01:19:01,635
Our names will be written
on a thousand walls,

776
01:19:01,840 --> 01:19:06,231
our crimes told and retold
by our faithful believers.

777
01:19:07,240 --> 01:19:11,119
We shall die together
in front of their very eyes

778
01:19:11,320 --> 01:19:14,949
and give them something
to be haunted by.

779
01:19:16,360 --> 01:19:19,989
Come with me and be immortal.

780
01:19:27,840 --> 01:19:29,796
[cries out]

781
01:19:33,000 --> 01:19:34,956
[shrieks] No!

782
01:19:44,280 --> 01:19:45,235
No...

783
01:19:47,480 --> 01:19:49,436
[scrunching sound]

784
01:20:01,840 --> 01:20:03,796
[Candyman] Shh.

785
01:20:06,320 --> 01:20:07,753
Shh.

786
01:20:07,960 --> 01:20:10,235
You're mine now.

787
01:20:10,440 --> 01:20:13,876
It's time for a new miracle.

788
01:21:32,200 --> 01:21:35,192
[Candyman] <i>It was always you, Helen.</i>

789
01:21:35,400 --> 01:21:37,356
<i>It was always you.</i>

790
01:21:38,120 --> 01:21:40,076
[baby cries]

791
01:21:49,680 --> 01:21:51,318
[crying]

792
01:22:14,520 --> 01:22:16,476
[crying]

793
01:22:34,000 --> 01:22:35,956
[crying]

794
01:22:51,440 --> 01:22:53,112
He's here.

795
01:22:53,920 --> 01:22:55,876
[crying]

796
01:23:02,840 --> 01:23:04,796
[crying]

797
01:23:25,800 --> 01:23:27,074
I'm coming.

798
01:23:33,360 --> 01:23:36,033
- It's OK.
- [boy] Check it out, man.

799
01:23:38,520 --> 01:23:41,080
Oh... Yes.

800
01:23:43,160 --> 01:23:45,196
[man] What happened?

801
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:49,518
[Jake] Candyman's in there.
I saw him go in there. I saw his hook.

802
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:53,110
Candyman's in there!
I saw his hook!

803
01:23:53,320 --> 01:23:55,276
Shh.

804
01:23:58,400 --> 01:24:00,356
I knew you'd come.

805
01:24:02,280 --> 01:24:03,349
Burn him.

806
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:06,956
[cheering]

807
01:24:08,400 --> 01:24:09,355
Hush.

808
01:24:09,560 --> 01:24:13,269
Burn him! Burn him! Burn him!

809
01:24:15,600 --> 01:24:17,556
[crowd chanting] Burn him!

810
01:24:19,440 --> 01:24:21,158
Help!

811
01:24:21,360 --> 01:24:24,079
Burn! Burn! Burn!

812
01:24:24,280 --> 01:24:26,430
Help! Help me!

813
01:24:26,640 --> 01:24:28,596
[cheering]

814
01:24:30,040 --> 01:24:32,315
You lied to me.

815
01:24:32,520 --> 01:24:35,830
We must be on our way now,
you and I.

816
01:24:36,040 --> 01:24:38,679
Our bones will soon be ashes,

817
01:24:38,880 --> 01:24:41,917
and we shall never be separated again.

818
01:24:42,720 --> 01:24:44,312
Let me go.

819
01:24:44,520 --> 01:24:48,069
I cannot.
We are already dead.

820
01:24:48,680 --> 01:24:50,636
[baby cries]

821
01:24:56,760 --> 01:25:00,833
Helen! [screaming]

822
01:25:09,800 --> 01:25:14,316
[screaming, grunting]

823
01:25:31,240 --> 01:25:33,117
Come back to me!

824
01:25:44,360 --> 01:25:45,998
Come back!

825
01:25:48,560 --> 01:25:50,516
[baby cries]

826
01:26:08,880 --> 01:26:10,791
[groaning, screaming]

827
01:26:53,360 --> 01:26:55,715
We commend to Almighty God
our sister Helen

828
01:26:55,920 --> 01:26:57,956
and commit her body to the ground.

829
01:26:58,160 --> 01:27:00,390
Earth to earth, ashes to ashes,

830
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:02,556
dust to dust.

831
01:27:02,760 --> 01:27:06,878
The Lord bless her and keep her
and give her peace.

832
01:27:07,080 --> 01:27:11,312
God of holiness and power, accept our
prayers on behalf of your servant Helen.

833
01:27:11,520 --> 01:27:13,476
Do not call her deeds against her,

834
01:27:13,680 --> 01:27:16,717
for in her heart
she desired to do your will.

835
01:27:16,920 --> 01:27:21,630
Almighty God, bless you, the Father
and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

836
01:27:30,040 --> 01:27:31,996
[man] My God.
Look at that.

837
01:27:34,400 --> 01:27:36,356
[Purcell] Trevor?

838
01:28:47,480 --> 01:28:49,436
[Stacey] Trevor?

839
01:28:50,040 --> 01:28:52,554
What is it?

840
01:28:52,760 --> 01:28:56,355
- Trevor, are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

841
01:28:58,160 --> 01:29:00,116
Aren't you hungry?

842
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:03,829
No, I'm OK. I'll eat later.

843
01:29:04,040 --> 01:29:06,873
I was gonna make us a nice dinner.

844
01:29:07,080 --> 01:29:09,036
OK. Whatever.

845
01:29:50,920 --> 01:29:53,150
Hey, why don't you help me
make the salad?

846
01:29:54,720 --> 01:29:56,711
OK. I'll be there in a minute.

847
01:30:17,440 --> 01:30:19,396
Oh, Helen...

848
01:30:24,240 --> 01:30:26,196
Helen...

849
01:30:31,720 --> 01:30:33,676
Helen.

850
01:30:39,040 --> 01:30:40,758
Helen.

851
01:30:41,560 --> 01:30:42,993
Ow!

852
01:30:47,200 --> 01:30:50,158
What's the matter, Trevor?

853
01:30:50,360 --> 01:30:52,316
Scared of something?

854
01:30:53,880 --> 01:30:57,873
[groaning, gurgling]

855
01:30:58,080 --> 01:31:00,958
- [shrieking, gagging]
- [Helen sighs]

856
01:31:01,160 --> 01:31:03,310
Trevor...

857
01:31:03,520 --> 01:31:05,476
My God, Trevor?

858
01:31:06,200 --> 01:31:07,553
Trevor?

859
01:31:08,600 --> 01:31:09,999
Trevor?

860
01:31:10,200 --> 01:31:12,634
[screaming]


